The paper deals with facial expression recognition using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper focuses on recognizing facial expressions in a difficult setting with severe occlusions, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of intentionally occluded training examples to improve accuracy also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
